## Naming
- All files: lowercase-kebab-case.js
- All classes: PascalCase
- All constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- All variables/functions: camelCase
- Module format: CommonJS (require/module.exports) — no ESM/CJS mixing

## No Magic Numbers
- Every threshold MUST use phi-math: phiThreshold(level), CSL_THRESHOLDS.*, PSI, PHI
- Every collection size MUST use Fibonacci: fib(n)
- Every timing MUST use phiBackoff() or phi-scaled intervals
- Every weight MUST use phiFusionWeights(n) or phiResourceWeights(n)
- BANNED: Hardcoded 0.5, 0.7, 0.8, 0.85, 0.9, 0.95, 100, 500, 1000, 5000
- BANNED: Priority enums (CRITICAL, HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW) for work classification
- USE INSTEAD: CSL-gated cosine similarity for relevance routing

## No Localhost
- BANNED: localhost, 127.0.0.1, hardcoded ports in production code
- USE INSTEAD: process.env.PORT, process.env.HOST, domain-based routing
- All URLs must use branded Heady domains (headyme.com, headyapi.com, etc.)

## No Console.log
- BANNED: console.log, console.warn, console.error in production
- USE INSTEAD: createLogger(serviceName) from core/heady-logger.js
- All logs MUST be structured JSON with correlation IDs

## CORS Policy
- BANNED: Access-Control-Allow-Origin: '*' in production
- USE INSTEAD: Explicit origin whitelist from ALLOWED_ORIGINS env var

## Health Endpoints
- REQUIRED: Every service MUST expose /health or /healthz
- REQUIRED: Health response includes service name, version, uptime, coherence score
- REQUIRED: Dependency health checks (database, cache, upstream services)

## Error Handling
- BANNED: Empty catch blocks: catch (e) {}
- BANNED: Generic error messages without context
- REQUIRED: Typed AppError class with statusCode, code, details
- REQUIRED: All async operations wrapped in try/catch

## Code Completeness
- BANNED: TODO, FIXME, HACK, XXX comments
- BANNED: Placeholder implementations or stub functions
- BANNED: "exercise for the reader" patterns
- REQUIRED: Every function is complete and production-ready

## Security
- Secrets: ONLY from process.env or HeadySecretService — never hardcoded
- Input: ALL user input validated and sanitized before use
- Auth: JWT with short expiry + refresh mechanism
- Cookies: httpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Strict
- Rate limiting: Required on all public endpoints

## Dependencies
- Pin ALL dependencies to exact versions (no ^, no ~)
- Maximum 3 runtime dependencies (prefer zero-dep implementations)
- Audit: npm audit clean before merge

## Testing
- Critical paths MUST have tests
- Health endpoints MUST have integration tests
- Error paths MUST be tested

## Bee Lifecycle
- All bees MUST implement: spawn(), execute(), report(), retire()
- All bees MUST emit telemetry via telemetry-bee channel
- All bees MUST register with bee-factory on spawn
- All bees MUST deregister on retire
- All bee parameters MUST use phi-scaling

## Shutdown
- REQUIRED: Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM and SIGINT
- REQUIRED: LIFO cleanup order for registered resources
- REQUIRED: Connection draining before exit
